- var currentPage = 'Notifications & Alerts'
doctype html
html(lang='en')
  include ./includes/_head
  body
    include ./includes/_sidebarNav
    .main-content.container-fluid
      h1 Notifications &amp; Alerts
      .row
        .col-sm-4
          img.img-responsive(src='./img/section-alerts-intro-img.png')
        .col-sm-8
          h2 Errors
          p Errors occur when an app fails to complete an expected action

          h3 Examples of Errors
          ul.list-unstyled
            li When user input is not understood
            li An app failing to load
            li Incompatible operations are run concurrently
            li Success
            li Failure
            li Information
            li And success messages

          h2 Notifications
          p Notifications provides quick, immediate updates about your account activities—particularly posts related to you and your activities.

          h3 Examples of notifications
          ul.list-unstyled
            li Success
            li Failure
            li Information

      .row
        .col-sm-4
          img.img-responsive(src='./img/section-alerts-inline-error.svg')
        .col-sm-4
          img.img-responsive(src='./img/section-alerts-page-top-error.svg')
        .col-sm-4
          img.img-responsive(src='./img/section-alerts-page-top-inline-error.svg')

      .u-container-padding-md
        h2 Homepage stripe
        .row
          .col-sm-6
            img.img-responsive(src='./img/section-alerts-homepage-alert.svg')
          .col-sm-6

            h3 Usage
            p Only one alert may be displayed at a time. Most important alert should displayed which could be impacting global user base.

            h3 Behavior
            p Upon lauching the homepage very first time alert should be visible. After 6 seconds alert should slide up and 8 px of blue stripe should be still visible so users can access alert if they want. Hovering over the 8px strip should bring the alert back to visible state and hover out should hide it back.
            p Alert does not slide down automaticly If users go on the other pages of the site and return back to the homepage. Show 8px blue strip only.

            h4 Specs: Mobile &amp; desktop
            ul.list-unstyled
              li Single-line upto 50 characters.
              li Blue stripe: #17679f
              li Text: Small #ffffff
              li Auto hide in: 6 seconds after homepage is fully loaded
              li Strip still visible to access: 8px (no text)
              li Hover over &amp; out : Show &amp; hide
              li use full width

        .u-container-padding-sm
          .global-nav.global-nav--alert-example
            .global-nav__alert-stripe
              .global-nav__alert-stripe-content
                p Pay attention to me! I've got something important to tell you.
            .global-nav__utility-bar
              img.global-nav__logo.hidden-xs(src='img/pbc-logo.svg')
              img.global-nav__logo.visible-xs(src='img/pbc-logo-mobile.svg')
              ul.global-nav__utility-bar-links
                li
                  a #[span.icon-home]
                    span.hidden-xs Dashboard
                li
                  a #[span.icon-notification]
                    span.hidden-xs Notifications
                li
                  a #[span.icon-user]
                    span.hidden-xs First&nbsp;name
                li
                  a #[span.icon-phone]
                    span.hidden-xs Contact&nbsp;us
            .global-nav__main
                ul.global-nav__section-links
                  li
                    a Item 1
                  li.selected
                    a Item 2
                  li
                    a Item 3
                  li
                    a Item 4
                  li
                    a Item 5
                  li
                    a Item 6

      h2 Notifications

      h3 Usage
      p Notifications provides quick, immediate updates about your account activities—particularly posts related to you and your activities.

      h3 Types of Notifications
      ul.list-unstyled
        li Generic account activities
        li Claim updates
        li Payment due
        li Any healthcare changes that user need to know
        li Secure messaging notifications
        li Renewal notice
        li Upcoming appointments

      h3 Behavior
      p Notifications should never be replaced with any alerts, dialogs or snackbar related informations. A notification would always have a destination where user can get more information or take any action.

      h3 States
      ul.list-unstyled
        li read
        li not read

    include ./includes/_scripts
    script(src='./js/alerts.js')
